{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"183d71b1-ad47-49ba-aabf-c4a3926bae5d","content":"Here's the recommended MSTest setup:\n\n## 1. Project file (`YourTests.csproj`)\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.7\">\n\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n\n</Project>\n```\n\n`MSTest.Sdk` pulls in the test framework, runner, and Microsoft.Testing.Platform — no extra NuGet references needed.\n\n## 2. Enable parallel execution (`AssemblyInfo.cs` or any file)\n\n```csharp\n[assembly: Parallelize(Scope = ExecutionScope.ClassLevel)]\n```\n\nThis runs test **classes** in parallel (safest default). Use `ExecutionScope.MethodLevel` if your tests are fully isolated.\n\n## 3. Make database tests sequential\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\n[DoNotParallelize]\npublic class DatabaseIntegrationTests\n{\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void Can_Insert_Record() { /* ... */ }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void Can_Read_After_Write() { /* ... */ }\n}\n```\n\nThe `[DoNotParallelize]` attribute on the class forces those tests onto the main thread, running sequentially after all parallel work completes.\n\n---\n\n**Summary:**\n\n| Concern | Mechanism |\n|---------|-----------|\n| Minimal project | `MSTest.Sdk` (single SDK reference) |\n| Parallel by default | `[assembly: Parallelize]` |\n| Sequential DB tests | `[DoNotParallelize]` on the class |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1f25a163-28ad-4609-8386-4df70b917b62","outputTokens":384,"requestId":"BD04:7B45F:1E3313A:223AAE1:6A07CEF2"},"id":"5ceaa80a-3bc6-4b71-a1e2-ceb1ddaa2174","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:57:15.715Z","parentId":"3cc13075-139a-4641-964d-01d4a77da8fa"}
